title: What is CS1501?
labels: All compiler errors have to be fixed

sections.title: Symptoms
content: • When trying to enter play mode, I am receiving the error below:
error CS1501: No overload for method `___' takes `___' arguments

sections.title: Cause
content: The CS1501 error is caused when a method is being invoked but is not being passed the correct number of arguments.
In this example we are trying to invoke a method that takes two arguments but we are not passing the method any arguments.
Here is how the error appears in this example:
error CS1501: No overload for method `DestroyAnEnemy' takes `0' arguments

sections.title: Resolution
content: The error CS1501 is resolved by ensuring that the correct number of arguments are being passed into the method being invoked.
